cyclone.name: ZETA
cyclone.current_location: about 210 miles SE of Cozumel, Mexico
cyclone.trajectory: Moving northwest and expected to turn north-north-east across the central Gulf, aiming at the northern Gulf Coast (southeast Louisiana/Mississippi) mid-week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: southeast Louisiana coast, near or just south of New Orleans

weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern Gulf Coast from Louisiana to Alabama
weather_observation.wind: Tropical-storm-force winds (40–50 mph with higher gusts) likely by Wednesday evening.
weather_observation.storm_surge: Potential storm surge 3–5 ft along the lower Mississippi River delta and adjacent coast.
weather_observation.rainfall: 2–4 inches with isolated 6 inches; flash and urban flooding possible.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Stronger river currents, debris, and temporary navigation restrictions along the Mississippi River channel.
